{"word":"εὐπρόσωπος","slug":"εὐπρόσωπος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐπρόσωπος</b></el> <el>(εὐ-πρόσωπος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πρόσωπον'><el>πρόσωπον</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>fair of face</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: <i>with glad countenance</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>fair in outward show, specious</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}